<div class='outer_container'>
  <h1 class='steps_to_share'>Steps to Share your Data</h1>
  <div class='left_container'>
    <div class='steps_to_publish'>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <span>1. Prepare</span><br/>
          Gather your data and information. <%= link_to 'Preparing to Submit', stash_engine.preparing_to_submit_path %>
        </li>
        <li>
          <span>2. Describe Data</span><br/>
          Create your metadata. <%= link_to 'Metadata Entry Basics', stash_engine.metadata_basics_path %>
        </li>
        <li>
          <span>3. Upload Data</span><br/>
          Add your data to Stash. <%= link_to 'Upload Basics', stash_engine.upload_basics_path %>
        </li>
        <li>
          <span>4. Get Confirmation</span><br/>
          Receive notification of successful deposit.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class='begin'>
      <%= link_to 'Begin', dashboard_path, class: 'o-banner__button' %>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class='right_container'>
    <h3 class='why_share'>Why Share?</h3>
    <div class='get_started_points'>
      <ul>
        <li>Promotes transparency and reproducibility in research.</li>
        <br/>
        <li>Increases the visibility of underlying research (69% increase in citations for articles associated with shared datasets, Piwowar et al. 2007, doi:10.1371/journal.pone.0000308).</li>
        <br/>
        <li>Allows you to get credit for your datasetâ€”add it to your CV, share it with colleagues, and have others cite your dataset when using it.</li>
        <br/>
        <li>Helps you meet funder and publisher requirements for data availability.
            Increases chances for collaboration.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
      <p class='get_started_points'>For more information, see the <a href='http://www.data-archive.ac.uk/create-manage/planning-for-sharing/why-share-data'>UK Data Archive list of reasons to share data</a>.</p>
    </div>
</div>